cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper focuses on object recognition in real-world robotics applications using RGB-D data. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses learning with imperfect sensor data, which is a common problem in robotics, suggesting that it could also belong to the robotics category (cs.RO). The paper proposes a novel architecture for object recognition, indicating that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Finally, the paper leverages recent progress on Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), suggesting that it could also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) category.
